title: Suicide bombers target Uganda's capital Kampala
content: At least three people are killed in the blasts near parliament and the city's police HQ.

title: Polish forces tear-gas migrants at Belarus border
content: Poland's defence ministry says migrants were throwing stones and trying to destroy a border fence.

title: France clears major migrant camp amid UK tensions
content: About 1,500 people are evacuated near Dunkirk, as the UK and France vow to tackle illegal migration.

title: Pfizer to let poorer nations make new Covid pill
content: The US company will allow 95 developing nations to produce generic versions of its antiviral pill.

title: Russia says satellite missile test poses no threat
content: The US earlier said Russia "recklessly" destroyed a satellite, endangering astronauts in space.

title: Myanmar army adds charges against Aung San Suu Kyi
content: The ousted leader is accused of electoral fraud, as the junta insists she is being treated well.

title: Wife of Mexico's most wanted cartel boss arrested
content: Rosalinda González is suspected of running the finances of her husband's Jalisco New Generation Cartel.
